[{"id":"VR797890","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two spheres, one a conducting sphere and the other an insulating sphere. Each sphere is on a stand, is connected by wire to ground, and has a negatively charged rod next to it.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR797890.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two spheres on insulating stands have the same diameter, but are made of different materials. One sphere is a conductor and the other is an insulator. Each sphere is connected to ground by a wire and is initially electrically neutral. As shown in the figure, identical, negatively charged insulating rods are brought equally close to each sphere. How are the net charges <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q sub c\"><math alttext=\"Q sub c\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>Q</mi><mtext>c</mtext></msub></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q sub i\"><math alttext=\"Q sub i\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>Q</mi><mtext>i</mtext></msub></math></span></span> on the conducting and insulating spheres, respectively, related when the negatively charged rods are close to the spheres? Assume that the two setups are far enough apart that they do not affect each other.</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR797890_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q sub c is greater than Q sub i\"><math alttext=\"Q sub c is greater than Q sub i\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>Q</mi><mtext>c</mtext></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>Q</mi><mtext>i</mtext></msub></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q sub i is greater than Q sub c\"><math alttext=\"Q sub i is greater than Q sub c\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>Q</mi><mtext>i</mtext></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>Q</mi><mtext>c</mtext></msub></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q sub c equals, Q sub i, which is greater than 0\"><math alttext=\"Q sub c equals, Q sub i, which is greater than 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>Q</mi><mtext>c</mtext></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>Q</mi><mtext>i</mtext></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q sub Q equals Q sub i, which equals 0\"><math alttext=\"Q sub Q equals Q sub i, which equals 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>Q</mi><mtext>c</mtext></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>Q</mi><mtext>i</mtext></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":0}]